"Ribeiro S.K., Younes-Lbrahim P.S.","Global warming and transport in Brazil - Ethanol alternative",2001,"International Journal of Vehicle Design","27","1-4",,"118","128",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0035706787&partnerID=40&md5=abae49c2a2af6020860436194b632af9","PET/COPPE/UFRJ, Federal Univ. of Rio de Janeiro, Centro de Tecnologia, Bloco H sala H111, Ilha do Fundao, CEP 21945-970, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil","Ribeiro, S.K., PET/COPPE/UFRJ, Federal Univ. of Rio de Janeiro, Centro de Tecnologia, Bloco H sala H111, Ilha do Fundao, CEP 21945-970, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil; Younes-Lbrahim, P.S., PET/COPPE/UFRJ, Federal Univ. of Rio de Janeiro, Centro de Tecnologia, Bloco H sala H111, Ilha do Fundao, CEP 21945-970, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil","This paper deals with the risk of global warming as intensified by the carbon dioxide (CO2) emissions of the transport sector, particularly in gasoline-powered vehicles in Brazil. Car ownership and use are increasing rapidly partly because of very poor public transport quality, which, in turn, is causing higher emission levels of CO2. In this connection, the use of ethanol in Brazil for the transport sector may prove to be an important alternative, furthering the efforts to stabilise the actual level of gases in the atmosphere. The energy derived from biomass, and in this case, from a renewable, 'clean' source, i.e., from sugar-cane, has the unquestionable advantage of permitting the almost complete reabsorption of CO2 emitted through the combustion of fuel alcohol. This closed cycle allows, in principle, the increase of the energy supply, essential for economic development, with fewer hazards to the environment.","Air pollution; Ethanol; Global warming; Transport","Air pollution; Biomass; Carbon dioxide; Combustion; Ethanol; Gas absorption; Motor transportation; Particulate emissions; Gasoline powered vehicles; Global warming",,,,,,"(1999) Balanço Energético Nacional, 1998, p. 153. , Ministério das Minas e Energia, Brasilia; (1999) Anuário Estatistico, 26, p. 333. , Ministério dos Transportes. Brasilia; (1999) Anuário Estatistico 1957/1998, , São Paulo; Ribeiro, S.K., (1995) Uso Energético dos Produtos de Cana de Açúcar como Instrumento do Brasil em Negociações Internationais para Redução de Emissão de Gases de Efeito Estufa, p. 235. , DSc. Thesis, Federal University of Rio de Janeiro, COPPE, Rio de Janeiro; (1999) Proconve/Cetesb, , Ministério do Meio Ambiente, Brasilia; Macedo, I.C., (1997) Greenhouse Gas Emissions and Bio-Ethanol Production/Utilization in Brazil, , IR/CTC -05/97, Piracicaba; (1996) Greenhouse Gas Inventory Reporting Instructions - IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas, Inventories, 1-3. , IPCC, IEA, OECD","Ribeiro, S.K.; PET/COPPE/UFRJ, Federal Univ. of Rio de Janeiro, Centro de Tecnologia, Bloco H sala H111, Ilha do Fundao, CEP 21945-970, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil; email: skr@pet.coppe.ufrj.br",,,,,,,,01433369,,IJVDD,,"English","Int J Veh Des",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0035706787
